name: Semantic Segmentation with Masks
model_desc: The Segment Anything Model (SAM) is an AI tool by Meta AI that enables computers to identify and segment objects in images based on visual prompts without requiring retraining the model. SAM can segment objects by selecting points on them or drawing bounding boxes around them.

name: Automatic License Plate Recognition
model_desc: Automatic License Plate Recognition (ALPR) technology enables accurate and fast recognition of license plates in various conditions, including dark, blurry images, and different angles. It provides detailed vehicle information such as make, model, color, and region, making it valuable for applications like parking enforcement, toll collection, and vehicle monitoring. ALPR systems like SAM and others offer real-time processing, self-learning capabilities, and location optimization, enhancing efficiency and accuracy in vehicle-related tasks.

name: Automatic Speech Recognition using Segments

name: Sound Event Detection

name: Signal Quality Detection
model_desc: he Signal Quality Detection model is a real-time monitoring system that detects distortions and anomalies in GPS signals by utilizing additional monitoring correlators to recognize and correct signal degradation, ensuring accurate navigation and location services.

name: Visual Ranker
model_desc: Here is a demo that showcases how to construct an interface enabling users to drag, arrange, and rank responses from different Large Language Models (LLMs) and chatbot systems based on their relevance to a specified prompt and their perceived bias, thus facilitating an intuitive and visual understanding of how well these AI systems align with the topic and the degree of subjective interpretation they exhibit.

name: Supervised Language Model Fine-tuning
model_desc: Collecting labeled text data for training an initial LLM, focusing on task-specific performance improvement. This stage involves gathering instructions and responses to adapt the base model to a wide range of tasks, enhancing its ability to generate more accurate and useful responses.

name: Chatbot Model Assessment
model_desc: Collecting expert assessments of LLM-generated responses for quality assurance and model evaluation. This stage involves evaluating the model's responses based on criteria like correctness, relevance, and safety, which provides valuable feedback for further model refinement and helps ensure the final LLM meets desired performance standards.
